To use a type assertion, you can add a colon followed by the desired type after the variable name, like this:

```typescript
let someValue: string | number;
// Here we tell the compiler that we know someValue is a string, even though it could also be a number
let str = someValue as string;
```

This tells the TypeScript compiler that even though someValue is declared as having multiple possible types (string | number), we know that it will only ever be a string. The compiler will then treat someValue as if it were always a string, and will not give any type errors when using it as such.

